Now what says the Regular Joe’s Guide like a salad place, eh? Huh??? Yea yea, I know, but the Sweetgreen chain is different. The RJG has always frowned on places like Sweet Tomatoes, where it’s one big salad bar, and most people end up eating 10 times the calories than they would have had they just indulged in a double cheeseburger with fries. It just sounds healthy, but by the time they’re done loading it up with ranch dressing, tons of cheese, bacon, and whatever else they can find that isn’t good for you – then you still need to be wheeled out of there. We Americans can’t help it. All-you-can-eat buffets are a magnet for our appetites, and we all feel an obligation to “break even” with the restaurant, and load up as many times as possible. Sweetgreen is none of that. In fact, it’s basically a Chipotle for salads. That is to say, it’s assembly line styled.

If an organic, healthy, highly nutrtitious salad, with warm savory flavors that make you feel all cozy inside is more important than the atmosphere, this is the perfect place to be. It's one of my most favorite places to get the best "warm" (cuz of the warm quinoa and sauteed mushrooms I add to my Create Your Own) salad. Granted, there is no "ambiance" for dining; just a metal and glass kitchen area with fixins, a wood bench/chairs and tables along the wall for a place to enjoy your salad, and light conversation, or your phone. In case you would like to try my "Create Your Own": I start with the mesclun (mixed greens), then add quinoa, cilantro, sweet potatoes, carrots, avocado, red onion, hard boiled egg, sauteed mushrooms, and nori (with seasoned sunflower seeds) with the Pesto dressing, "heavy". Yummmmm!!! Love it! Don't knock it till you try it. :-) Enjoy!!! I do, every time.

This  cold , stark place  looks  like   a kitchen  in  a  prison.If  you  have   gotten  to  the  point   where  you  are looking  at  your  iPhone  23  hours  a  day,this  place  has  the  right  atmosphere ....none.For  $9.50 you  can  get  a  bowl of  lettuce,and  if  you  are  lucky ,you  may  find  a  piece of tomato  in  it.The  servers look  like  they  just  got  out  of  prison or  are  still  in  for  the  night  hours.If  you  like  salt  or  pepper,it  is  not  anywhere that  you  can  place  it  in  your  salad.You  have  to  ask  permission  from  one  of  the  guards and  she  places  the  amount  on  it  that  she  thinks  is  best.Sugar for your  choice  of  six  different   "drinks " that  you  can  purchase  from  the  dirty  dishwater  machine,is  non  existent.When  I  said  the  word  "sugar for  the  tea",they  looked  at  me  like  I  had  seven  eyes and  shook  their  heads.The  drinks,and  I  tried  all  of  them,were  nothing  but  tasteless colored  water.The  chairs and benches were  all wood  and very  uncomfortable..but  what  do  you  expect  from  a  prison.?Try  this  dump  if  you   want  to   make  believe  that  you  have  been  incarcerated.It  seems  like  the  owners  are  trying  to  portray  the  fact   that  if  you  eat nothing,you  will  be  slim  and  trim.They  even  put  the  exact  number  of  grams  of  sugar in the  drinks ,11 12   or  14,on  the  dispenser.Never  think  about  going  over  14 ..or  you  will  explode.This  place  is  a  scam.I  would  never  set  foot  in  this hole again.

Its places like this that are really changing the game when it comes to eating healthy. Sweetgreen is not only a friendly place to get your health on but its an environment that makes you want to eat healthy. Its really hard to eat unhealthy here, but if you want to its certainly possible. I have committed to a lifestyle change of eating healthy in the last two months and i am going strong because of sweetgreen. I enjoy a salad for lunch at least 3 times a week, i try to get their as much as a i can. Its weird it feels like my "safe zone" with food because i know its really hard to eat unhealthy.  I really enjoy their cucumber tahini dressing, its very tangy and really compliments my custom prepared bowl of awesomeness. I really appreciate the amount of effort that the company takes to ensure quality ingredients along with a flawless and efficient process. YES sometimes you have to wait, but the fact that you want to wait and so many other people are waiting should indicate how powerful this place is. I feel great since i have changed my eating habits and lifestyle and thankful for having a sweetgreen so close by!
